In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims June as Great Outdoors Month in the United States. He highlights the importance of America's natural beauty and the need to protect and experience these landscapes. Obama mentions the America's Great Outdoors Initiative, which aims to involve Americans in conservation and outdoor recreation. The initiative includes increasing recreational access to public lands, developing urban parks and community green spaces, and creating a new Conservation Service Corps for young people. The administration will work with various stakeholders to implement these recommendations. Additionally, Obama mentions the First Lady's "Let's Move!" initiative, which encourages youth to enjoy outdoor activities. He calls on all Americans to protect and explore the great outdoors and uphold the nation's legacy of conservation.